The paper discusses testing-based software analysis methodologies for discovering information leaks in complex software, specifically timing leaks in cryptographic implementations. This falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) as well as software engineering (cs.SE) since the paper proposes a new tool for software testing. The paper also mentions the use of coverage-guided greybox fuzzers, which relates to programming languages (cs.PL) and systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the empirical results presented in the paper involve machine learning techniques, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG).
